						               													<description>The official board game of Zecchino d'Oro: a TV Show competition where small children sing a song.&amp;#10;Players have to perform some tests to earn tiles to complete their mini puzzles.&amp;#10;The current player rolls the die and, depending on the square he lands, perform one of the following tests:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Answer to a curiosity concerning the Zecchino d'Oro and its most famous songs;&amp;#10;     Complete the verse of a song, choosing one of three options proposed;&amp;#10;     Sing, mime or draw a song, so the other players can guess it;&amp;#10;     Draw 2 cards with images and invents a verse by being inspired by them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If the test is successful, the current player can find out 2 tiles placed on the table: if they belong to his minipuzzle, he can keep them, otherwise he puts them in their place, always face down. Anyone can try to remember the location of their tiles, to discover them during his turn.&amp;#10;The player who completes their mini puzzle first, is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
